HEADWORD: Caloricity
<hw>Cal`o*ric"ity</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>A faculty in animals of developing and preserving the heat
necessary to life, that is, the animal heat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

